com.hazelcast.cluster.impl

Class VectorClock

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hazelcast.cluster.impl.VectorClock
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataSerializable, IdentifiedDataSerializable

    public class VectorClock
extends Object
implements IdentifiedDataSerializable
    Vector clock consisting of distinct replica logical clocks.

    See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vector_clock The vector clock may be read from different thread but concurrent updates must be synchronized externally. There is no guarantee for concurrent updates.

    • Method Detail

      • getTimestampForReplica

        public Long getTimestampForReplica(String replicaId)
        Returns logical timestamp for given replicaId. This method may be called from different threads and the result reflects the latest update on the vector clock.

      • setReplicaTimestamp

        public void setReplicaTimestamp(String replicaId,
                                long timestamp)
        Sets the logical timestamp for the given replicaId. This method is not thread safe and concurrent access must be synchronized externally.

      • merge

        public void merge(VectorClock other)
        Merges the provided vector clock into this one by taking the maximum of the logical timestamps for each replica. This method is not thread safe and concurrent access must be synchronized externally.

      • isAfter

        public boolean isAfter(VectorClock other)
        Returns true if this vector clock is causally strictly after the provided vector clock. This means that it the provided clock is neither equal to, greater than or concurrent to this vector clock. This method may be called from different threads and the result reflects the latest update on the vector clock.

      • isEmpty

        public boolean isEmpty()
        Returns true if this vector clock is empty (there are no logical timestamps for any replica). This method may be called from different threads and the result reflects the latest update on the vector clock.

      • entrySet

        public Set<Map.Entry<String,Long>> entrySet()
        Returns a set of replica logical timestamps for this vector clock.
